                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1098">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.20 Defense (M) Peru/9–1445: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Perw</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Pawley</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lima</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-09-14">September 14,
                            1945</date>.<lb/>[Received 3:45 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>951. Reurtel 871, 12th.<note n="72" xml:id="d1098fn72">Not printed; it referred
                        to draft note enclosed with instruction 25, August 7, <hi rend="italic"
                            >supra</hi>.</note> Suggested note to Peruvian Government was delivered
                    personally by me on August 20 to Ministry for Foreign <pb facs="1355" n="1341"
                        xml:id="pg_1341"/> Affairs which to date has not acknowledged same. Since
                    note simply gave notice it is possible no reply will be received.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Pawley</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
